      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NOCTURNAL (4) had been producing some good efforts this campaign so deserved the last-start win, working forward from a wider barrier to lead before saluting by close to 5m at this circuit and distance. Can push forward again from this draw and looks nicely placed to deliver again. THIS IS HEAVEN (5) has been solid in two outings here since a Penrith win, placing behind NOCTURNAL last time. Draws outside that rival so it won't be easy to turn the tables but he can be competitive again. BLAZING HIGH (9) draws wide but found winning form at this circuit and distance last week. He'll be at his peak now so with even luck could go on with it. YOU ARE MY WISH (10) is another that may need things to go his way given the outside draw but he was good when runner-up to NOCTURNAL last time. LOCHINVAR MARCELLO (7) deserves respect off a string of wins and placings, overcoming a back row draw to score at Penrith last time out.",
